# Dataset Overview

Dataset: `tartu_risk_dataset_annelinn_nightlife_zone_1`

This CSV is a synthetic hourly panel dataset for Tartu public-order incident
forecasting. One row is one district at one timestamp. The target is
`incident_count`; there is no `risk_score` and no `same_slot_avg_90d`.

## Basic Shape

- Rows: 38,880
- Columns: 18
- Districts: 18
- Hourly timestamps: 2,160
- Time range: 2026-01-28 00:00:00 to 2026-04-27 23:00:00
- Daily incident mean: 43.26
- Daily incident range: 26 to 74

## Columns

`id`, `area`, `time`, `population`, `area_km2`, `area_population_density`, `foot_traffic`, `area_type`, `socially_vulnerable_zone`, `minorities_zone`, `student_zone`, `nightlife_zone`, `day_of_week`, `hour`, `is_weekend`, `is_night`, `weather`, `incident_count`

## Additional Notes

- No extra synthetic-control fields beyond the core schema
- Non-target predictors in this file: `population`, `area_km2`, `area_population_density`, `foot_traffic`, `area_type`, `socially_vulnerable_zone`, `minorities_zone`, `student_zone`, `nightlife_zone`, `day_of_week`, `hour`, `is_weekend`, `is_night`, `weather`

## Target Behavior

- Zero rows: 91.52%
- Rows with exactly one incident: 7.24%
- Rows with two or more incidents: 1.24%
- Highest incident day: 2026-03-28 with 74 incidents
- Lowest incident day: 2026-03-05 with 26 incidents
- Feb 23 total: 45 incidents
- Feb 24 total: 51 incidents

The target is intentionally sparse: most district-hour combinations have no
incident, single incidents are occasional, and 2+ counts are uncommon.

## Strongest Aggregate Patterns

- Highest-total districts: Kesklinn (1097), Annelinn (673), Ülejõe (536), Karlova (410), Vaksali (309)
- Lowest-total districts: Variku (48), Raadi-Kruusamäe (46), Ihaste (36), Kvissentali (18), Maarjamõisa (12)
- Weekday daily means: Monday 39.1, Tuesday 36.6, Wednesday 36.3, Thursday 38.3, Friday 51.2, Saturday 58.0, Sunday 42.8
- Weather mix: clear 33.6%, rain 27.8%, snow 20.6%, storm 10.3%, other_extremes 7.8%

